<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Distribution and biotope.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
Found in the North Atlantic from Ireland and Britain, south to Portuguese shores (
<bibRefCitation author="Nobre, A" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Zoologia da Universidade do Porto, Porto" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" title="Moluscos marinhos de Portugal, Vol. 1." year="1931">Nobre 1931</bibRefCitation>
), Azores, Madeira, Selvagens (
<bibRefCitation author="Albuquerque, M" journalOrPublisher="Atlas das Ilhas Selvagens. Direccao Regional do Ambiente, Funchal" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" title="Moluscos marinhos." year="2009">Albuquerque et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), Canary Islands and throughout the Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Kaas 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" pagination="89 - 98" title="Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) procured by the CANCAP I-VII expeditions, 1976 - 86." volume="65" year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
). From the intertidal zone down to 50 m depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Van Belle, RA" journalOrPublisher="Gloria Maris" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" pagination="223 - 230" title="De Polyplacophora van de Azoren." volume="23" year="1984">Van Belle 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
